==English==

===Adverb===
'''diminuendo'''

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Italian ''diminuendo'', present participle of ''diminuere'', meaning "to shrink", "to diminish", or "to increase"

===Meanings===
#''Music.'' A musical term meaning that the volume of the notes gets gradually softer.
#A dynamic sign, shaped like an angle with the pointer on the right, indicating that the volume of the notes gets gradually softer.